    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the basa is cooking, return the<strong> drained potato & carrot</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, your <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a very generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth – this is your <strong>harissa mash</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't worry if your carrot doesn't get completely smooth, it will add some texture to your mash!</p>",
